race.comment: Open race. SIGIRIYA ROCK (11) is a horse who has always promised good ability, stepping up to 1700m second up this preparation and running out a strong winner at Geelong. Don't love the draw but he's open to further improvement and if they decide to be positive he'll go close. SKIPPERS CANYON (9) resumes. He was good in two Australian runs last time in, winning well fresh before rattling home here over 1800m. If he's fit enough he'll run well. NATION'S CALL (1) set up a strong speed at Flemington last week on very testing ground, sticking on quite well all things considered. This is easier and if he's come through that run okay he'll take catching. OPENING ADDRESS (3) has been solid in two runs back and should be ready to peak. POLITELY DUN (4) ran good splits from too far back fresh, wary although he may need a bit further.
